# Backend Rules — NestJS

## Technology

- NestJS + TypeScript
- TypeORM + PostgreSQL (keep TypeORM; do not migrate to Prisma unless user explicitly requests)
- `class-validator` DTOs on inputs
- Business logic in **services**, not controllers
- Global prefix: `/api`
- Default port: `3001` (see `main.ts`)

## Implemented modules (`backend/src/`)

```text
auth/                 # register, login, JWT
users/                # profile, student_profiles
universities/         # CRUD + search
majors/               # CRUD; university-major entity lives here
cutoff-scores/        # query by university/major (+ method filter); POST/PATCH/DELETE
admission-methods/    # GET catalog (PT xét tuyển — tra cứu, không CRUD admin)
university-majors/    # CRUD liên kết ngành–trường
recommendations/      # POST recommend, GET my history
chatbot/              # POST chat, GET history + Ollama pipeline
ollama/               # OllamaService (classify, extract, generate)
import-excel.ts       # Excel → PostgreSQL; `--merge` / IMPORT_MERGE
```

## Planned (when asked)

```text
admin-guard/          # role-based guard for write endpoints
migrations/           # replace synchronize: true for production
```

## Controller conventions

- Use `@ApiTags`, `@ApiBearerAuth('JWT')` for Swagger where applicable.
- Public read endpoints: universities, majors, cutoff list by university/major.
- Protected write/admin: POST/PUT/DELETE on master data; recommendations with save; chat history.
- Return consistent error messages; use NestJS exceptions (`NotFoundException`, etc.).

## DTO and validation

- Every POST/PUT body has a DTO class with validation decorators.
- Whitelist is enabled globally; unknown fields are stripped.

## Database access

- Use TypeORM repositories or query builder in services.
- Do not use `synchronize: true` in production; plan migrations when going to prod.
- Import script may use raw SQL via `DataSource` for bulk load (`import-excel.ts`).

## CORS

Allowed origins: `http://localhost:3000`, `http://localhost:3001` (Next.js dev).

## Environment variables (`backend/.env`)

```text
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_USERNAME=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=...
DB_NAME=university_recommend
JWT_SECRET=...
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
PORT=3001

# Planned for Ollama
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.1
```

## Key npm scripts

- `npm run start:dev` — development API
- `npm run import:excel` — reload master data from Excel (TRUNCATE master tables)
- `npm run build` / `npm run start:prod` — production

## Do not

- Put business rules only in controllers
- Add fake entities or endpoints not backed by PostgreSQL
- Call external paid LLM APIs
